<p><i>HS: Let's see...Saturday night I made two recipes that I've been working on for the new book. One was a hearty pasta dish, and another was a favorite (substantial) arugula salad. And then a big pile of grilled slabs of sesame bread rubbed with garlic. All in all pretty simple, and it worked for veg/non-vegetarians. Generally speaking, I try to make it a non-issue. People generally seem fine eating vegetarian or vegan meals as long as the food tastes good and is satisfying.</i></p></div></div>
